The paper presents a new type of probabilistic model based on neural networks, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The focus on neural networks and probabilistic modeling suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY), which are additional relevant sub-categories. The use of dissimilarity coefficients and the emphasis on task-specific loss functions suggest that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories.
